HEADWORD: Cerebrin
<hw>Cer"e*brin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Cerebrum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A
nonphosphorized, nitrogenous substance, obtained from brain and nerve
tissue by extraction with boiling alcohol. It is uncertain whether it
exists as such in nerve tissue, or is a product of the decomposition of
some more complex substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerebripetal</ent>⟦br⟧
